            <forecast-period start-time-local="2026-05-05T03:41:42+09:30" end-time-local="2026-05-05T03:41:42+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-05-04T18:11:42Z" end-time-utc="2026-05-04T18:11:42Z">
                <text type="synoptic_situation">A ridge of high pressure will begin to extend from the west on Tuesday and will be briefly be weakened as a cold front crosses the southeast on Wednesday afternoon. The ridge will begin to re-establish in the wake of the front and stabilise over SA with the slow moving high pressure centre sitting south of WA by Friday.</text>
                <text type="preamble">Wind and wave forecasts are averages. Wind gusts can be 40 per cent stronger than the forecast, and stronger still in squalls and thunderstorms. Maximum waves can be twice the forecast height.</text>
